or=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usharak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 9:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA Choices.</span><hr size=1> 1. Run 3<br>2. some other stuffs in general<br>3. ND 3<br>4. AOE Taunt<br>5. CS 3<br>6. CA 3<br>7. Ambidex<br>8. Playtime!<br><br>That is, if you are setting yourself up to be a primary tank for your guild.  If not, then choose what you think would make your life easier and more fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>The great thing about AAXP is that it does allow us to individualize ourselves just a bit.  The roadmap listed above is the one set for those that are MTing huge mobs for our guilds.  It is not a necessary one to follow. <p>Sharak'Duom 51 Ghost<br>Keroppi'Duom 60 Warlord</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usharak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharak</A> at: 6/25/02 9:13:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 9:18:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA Choices.</span><hr size=1> Thnx Sharak.<br><br>guess it makes sense to skip Regen 3 since I got a L60 Cleric playing by my side everytime <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Oh, btw, you listed CA 3 instead of my choice of CS 3. Is avoidance better than stability? [I notice 2 schools of thought here]<br><br>And CF 3 is not worth the points? I thought higher chances of Critting = higher chances of doing more dmg per swing?<br><br>And.. AoE taunt effectively taunts all the mobs around me.. if the mobs are all mezzed/rooted while I tank 1, won't this be effectively non-efficient? [unless in the case where we pull L55+ mobs and get 3 - 4, then maybe I go AOE taunt + defensive?] <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie - 60 Warrior<br>Morganna - 57 Cleric<br>Tiejinnie - Lurikeen NightShade<br>Legion of Avatars</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usharak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 9:38:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Both</span><hr size=1> Both CS3 and CA3 are good skills to have (they are both up there :-p ).  No real preference which is better/worse, if you plan on getting both, then I would suggest picking one and finishing it to the end, then going for the other.<br><br>CF3 wont give you the damage ouput gain that Ambidex will.  Unless you want to go for using a 2 hander primarily, in which case CF3 and Flurry is a better tree to branch off to (but a buttload of more points <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br><br>AoE taunt is a lifesaver.  No matter what the situation just about.  Quadding crazy mad raptor on your chanter due to resisted slows, smackin him/her around for 270 a pop?  AoE taunt it off.  MT transfer coming up?  AoE taunt it onto ya.  Your MT just bit it due to lag on the CH cycle?  Warn your clerics and AoE taunt when that first CH is incoming on ya.  Your rogue/monk puller just jammed 5 mobs on your group and your cleric just ripped a CH into them on incoming?  AoE taunt all those extra mobs off your cleric onto you (and pray <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Having a guarenteed taunt is so useful it isnt even funny <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 9:50:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1> kewl, point taken on those topics.<br><br>Think I'll finalize around:<br><br>1. Run3 [3points]<br>2. ND 3 [12 points]<br>3. CS 3 [12 points]<br>4. AE Taunt [5 points]<br>5. CF 3 [12 points]<br>6. Ambidextrous [9 points]<br>7. CA 3 [12 points]<br><br>Egads! That's a WHOPPING 65 points! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>That's gonna take me like what? 6 mths? bleh. <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie - 60 Warrior<br>Morganna - 57 Cleric<br>Tiejinnie - Lurikeen NightShade<br>Legion of Avatars</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukellaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 10:32:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Kell/fullsize/fighter.gif height=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1> I'd rather do run3 regen3 nd3 aet cs3 ca3 -&gt; then whatever you want. Unless you're willing to forgoe what will help you be a better tank for 30 points then ignore combat fury / flurry - big waste when you can be working cs ca. <br><br>Just my opinion. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108262>Kellaen</a>, 60 Warrior<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61537>Ayashii</a>, 60 Rogue<br>-Xegony</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 11:04:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1> nod, that's possible too.<br><br>but with my wife's Cleric always beside me, do I really need Regen3 still? Or is it good to have, but not a must to have for me?<br><br>Even when she's not at home, both PCs are side-by-side, so playing both at the same time are not a problem for me. <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie - 60 Warrior<br>Morganna - 57 Cleric<br>Tiejinnie - Lurikeen NightShade<br>Legion of Avatars</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 779<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 11:59:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1>  Gotta spend 6 points to get out of General skills. 3 run and you got 3 more to spend. Either spend em on stamina if you're low stam(will net you 36hp) or spend it on regen. I'd do regen. 30 free HP every minute adds up. <p><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/dumbsig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 12:36:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homex.coolconnect.com/member3/Tiejinnie/images/Avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1> Hmmm.... something new there.<br><br>So the first 6 points HAVE to go into General Archaic Abilities? It's like a pre-requisite to gain access to the rest?<br><br>Anyone tried bumping up Dex, Str, Agi or even Resists? And how effective are those?<br><br>Regen's kindda nice and all, but wanna see if other different paths yield good results too. <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie - 60 Warrior<br>Morganna - 57 Cleric<br>Tiejinnie - Lurikeen NightShade<br>Legion of Avatars</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukellaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 12:50:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Kell/fullsize/fighter.gif height=60 width=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Both</span><hr size=1> Well I don't have primal and my stats are pretty much all capped, save agility for any fight after buffs. I even regret spending 3 on stamina, would rather have done regen. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108262>Kellaen</a>, 60 Warrior<br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61537>Ayashii</a>, 60 Rogue<br>-Xegony</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaminy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taminy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/26/02 12:54:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1706.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AA Choices.</span><hr size=1> Yes you must spend six AA points in the general category before you can move on to the archetype category. Then you must spend 12 AA points in the archetype category before you can move on to the warrior class specific category.<br><br>Also, some abilities require other conditions to be met (ie you must have CF3 before you can start training Flurry). <br><br>I'm also going to echo what a few people have said here: I think regen3 is the best choice. It's the most worthwhile general ability (other than run3 of course). As Grimmlokk said, regen is 30 free hps every minute, and it won't suffer any kind of cap out effect like stamina eventually does. On the other hand though, this is your character, so if you want to get something different go ahead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><p><map name="FPMap0"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=207958" shape="rect" coords="98, 46, 245, 84"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=240522" shape="rect" coords="276, 49, 407, 86"><area href="http://www.dragonsfang.com/revolution/" shape="rect" coords="168, 8, 349, 46"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=240522" coords="411, 3, 497, 86" shape="rect"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=207958" shape="rect" coords="4, 3, 93, 86"></map><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/ssbbrothar/tamsig.jpg" usemap="#FPMap0" width="500" height="90"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 